name: Jesus May Ball 2017

musicEnts.name: Dance Core
musicEnts.description: Experience a masterclass in all things dance from the University dancesport team as they kick off the night, showing off their most famous numbers! If you're lucky you may catch a glimpse of them enjoying the ball themselves

musicEnts.name: B and the Jukeboys
musicEnts.description: You thought you’d seen the last of them last year... you thought wrong, see a Jesus favourite reunited again to sing covers of your favourite tunes.

musicEnts.name: Fickle Friends
musicEnts.description: Fickle Friends is an up and coming Indie Pop Band. They released their first single in 2014 and have since played over 50 festivals and a sold out tour. The band were described by NME as having "Bouncing synths, killer pop-hooks and on-point lyrics about modern alienation." A perfect way to spend the evening.

musicEnts.name: Laura Mvula
musicEnts.description: Innovative British singer-songwriter, two-time Mercury Prize nominee and two-time MOBO award winner. Her debut album, Sing to the Moon, was released in 2013 to critical acclaim. Her second album, The Dreaming Room, exceeded the success of her first and won the Ivor Novello Album Award 2017. Keep an eye on main stage for the highlight of this year’s May Ball season.

musicEnts.name: Truly Medly Deeply
musicEnts.description: Ex-cantabs TMD return with mashups of all your favourite tunes. Expect childhood nostalgia as well as all the latest hits

musicEnts.name: Julian Banks
musicEnts.description: Julian Banks is a world-renowned DJ who has worked with such artists as Aloe Blacc, Bone Thugs 'N Harmony, Capital Cities, and System Of A Down. He has played Coachella's Merv Griffin House next to A-Trak and Bonobo, and spun at some of the largest clubs in Europe including Croatia's famed Revelin Club.

musicEnts.name: Emma Folk Band
musicEnts.description: Instrumental and vocal pieces from British and Irish traditions. This band plays a wide range of dance music for ceilidhs, as well as songs and klezmer.
